b"We want to extend a heartfelt thank you to a very special McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s crew member, TQ, who went above and beyond to make sure a customer had an experience to remember. After Bonnie Kandel\xe2\x80\x99s 7-year old son Leif, who has autism, saw a classmate with a McDonald's Teen Titans Happy Meal toy at school he knew he wanted one for himself. When he and his mom walked into the Speedway, IN restaurant last week, they learned that the current Happy Meals toy was Lego Batman instead of the Teen Titans toy that Leif wanted so badly. Bonnie explained to TQ how much the toy meant to Leif and TQ quickly took action, working with her manager and taking time out of her day to find the toys for Leif. According to his mom, Leif\xe2\x80\x99s excitement was notable, he sleeps with them and takes them with him whenever they leave the house. 
 
Through her actions, TQ demonstrated to all of us that even the smallest things can make a big difference in the lives of other people. She showed us that she\xe2\x80\x99s not only a great crewmember who takes care of every customer, but also a great person who understands how inspiring kindness can be. TQ is an inspiration and McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s is proud to be a part of an amazing story!

We\xe2\x80\x99d also like to send a shout out to Love What Matters for sharing great stories like this that shine a light on the positive things that people do for each other. http://huff.to/2knrlLs"

b"We are so proud to recognize Kenny Soriano-Garcia, a crew member at one of Rod Lubeznik's Chicago restaurants, for going above and beyond his cashier responsibilities to help out a customer. Customer Destiny Carreno captured this moment and shared it with her social network. We were able to thank Kenny on Wednesday for his extraordinary customer service. Crew Members like Kenny embody the lovin\xe2\x80\x99 mentality shared by all of us at McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s. b"Today is the International Day of Peace \xe2\x80\x93 a day set aside by the United Nations to focus the world on peace and generate awareness for the need to eradicate war and violence.

To mark the day, McDonald's along with DreamWorks Animation, Google, Facebook, Twitter, Cargilll, McCain Foods, MasterCard, Burger King and United Airlines have joined to support the U.N.\xe2\x80\x99s World Food Programme and raise awareness and some much needed funding to fight hunger. Unfortunately, the need for help is growing every day. Right now, 60 million refugees have been forced from their homes as a result of war and conflict, more people than at any time since World War II. In just the past few weeks, the world has seen hundreds of thousands more people displaced. Half of the refugees are children\xe2\x80\xa6and all of them struggle daily with hunger.

The ad we\xe2\x80\x99ve created and its message about war and hunger will be shared on television and in digital placements in nearly 40 countries around the globe as we invite people to donate to the World Food Programme. I hope you\xe2\x80\x99ll share it with your friends and make a needed contribution so that those displaced can get the help they desperately need.

You can watch the ad below or here http://McD.to/peaceday

Thank you, Steve - McDonald's CEO"
